title.narrative: EDUCATION ENABLING ENVIRONMENT

description.narrative: By 2023 MoEYS at all levels has enhanced capacity to plan, execute and monitor results-based plans and budgets., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Evaluation, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, girls and boys, particularly the rural and urban poor, have increased access to inclusive, equitable, relevant and quality early childhood and basic education that promotes lifelong learning, including in emergencies.

title.narrative: By 2023 MoEYS at all levels has enhanced capacity to plan, execute and monitor results-based plans and budgets.

description.narrative: Amidst constraints due to COVID-19, the Capacity Development Partnership Fund (CDPF) continued to show flexibility in its ability to pivot and support the response and recovery efforts, building the capacities of MoEYS officials at all levels, including by adopting to alternative and online modalities. This enabled continued strategic support to result-oriented planning at the sector level in alignment with the Education Sector Plan and to develop and finalise key sectoral policy documents. Critical investments were made to strengthen teacher educators, develop scholarship systems, and improve data utilization at all levels. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
